Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.94,0:00:11.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,赛车运动的物流统筹是所有运动中最有挑战性的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.94,0:00:11.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,No sport is as logistically challenging as motorsports.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:11.66,0:00:13.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,诚然在所有运动中设备都很重要
Dialogue: 2,0:00:11.66,0:00:13.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,While equipment matters in any sport,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.58,0:00:16.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在赛车中 人只能算是半个运动员
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.58,0:00:16.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,in motorsports the human is only half the athlete
Dialogue: 1,0:00:16.76,0:00:18.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,而车是另一半
Dialogue: 2,0:00:16.76,0:00:18.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,—the vehicle is the other half.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:18.94,0:00:25.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,赛车的性能直接取决于在正确的时间正确的地点有没有正确的零件
Dialogue: 2,0:00:18.94,0:00:23.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,The performance of a motorsports vehicle is directly tied to having the right components
Dialogue: 2,0:00:23.50,0:00:25.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,in the right place at the right time
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.46,0:00:27.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以其背后的物流统筹也是比赛的一部分
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.46,0:00:27.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,so the logistics are part of the competition.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:27.90,0:00:31.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,赛车是一项运动 但也不全是娱乐 游戏之类
Dialogue: 2,0:00:27.90,0:00:31.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Racing may be a sport but it's not all fun and games.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.30,0:00:35.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为车队都是商业化的——意思是要恰饭的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.30,0:00:35.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Teams are businesses—businesses that are expected to make money.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.74,0:00:41.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,价值最高的F1车队——法拉利车队——值13亿美元
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.74,0:00:41.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,The most valuable Formula 1 team—Scuderia Ferrari—is worth over $1.3 billion.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.94,0:00:47.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,单一个车队就和Discord  Bird Rides  DoorDash这些科技公司等值
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.94,0:00:47.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,This means this team is valued at about as much as tech companies Discord, Bird Rides, or DoorDash.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.80,0:00:51.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,像法拉利这样有钱的车队可以在运输上花更多的钱
Dialogue: 2,0:00:47.80,0:00:51.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,The wealthier teams, like Ferrari, are able to spend more money on transport
Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.60,0:00:57.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,带更多设备和备件 当发生意外的时候容错性更高
Dialogue: 2,0:00:51.60,0:00:57.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,to bring more equipment and spare parts which can make the difference between winning and losing when things go wrong.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.12,0:01:01.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,F1赛事从各种方面来讲都是最具全球性的竞技赛事
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.12,0:01:01.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Formula 1 is by many measures the most international sports competition.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.66,0:01:07.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,每年21场比赛 车队们要在最短一周内频繁来往五大洲
Dialogue: 2,0:01:01.66,0:01:07.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Over its 21 yearly races the teams traverse five continents with as little as a week between events.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.84,0:01:13.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,每年都有无数卡车 船只 飞机参与这场赛事的运输物流工作
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.84,0:01:13.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,A chaotic ballet of trucks, boats, and planes transports this show across the world each year.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.90,0:01:15.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,参加F1的有10支车队
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.90,0:01:15.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ten teams compete in Formula 1,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:15.81,0:01:20.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,尽管比赛遍布全球 但其仍属于欧洲的赛事
Dialogue: 2,0:01:15.81,0:01:20.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,and despite it taking place worldwide it is by all measures a European sport.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:20.38,0:01:23.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,10支车队中8支是在欧洲注册并运营的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:20.38,0:01:23.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Eight of the ten teams are registered in and operate out of Europe.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:23.88,0:01:29.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,只有印度和美国的车队不在欧洲 但印度的车队基地在英国
Dialogue: 2,0:01:23.88,0:01:29.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Only the Indian and American teams are from elsewhere although, the Indian team is actually based in the UK
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.58,0:01:34.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,美国的车队基地在北卡罗来纳 但在英国还有第二基地在运营
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.58,0:01:34.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,while the US team, based in North Carolina, operates a secondary forward base in the UK
Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.50,0:01:39.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,以便于在欧洲比赛时员工不必在美国和欧洲来回跑
Dialogue: 2,0:01:34.50,0:01:39.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that its staff doesn't have to travel all the way back to the US between each of the European races
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.16,0:01:41.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,而最近几年欧洲的比赛几乎是连续的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.16,0:01:41.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,which in recent years have been held consecutively,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.34,0:01:45.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,除了大约在赛季中的夏天要去加拿大
Dialogue: 2,0:01:41.34,0:01:45.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,with the brief interruption of the Canadian Grand Prix, in the middle of the season over summer.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.62,0:01:50.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,也多亏如此 相比于其他地点 在欧洲的比赛物流统筹上更容易一些
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.62,0:01:50.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,Thanks to this, the European leg of the season is, compared to the rest, relatively easy logistically
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.84,0:01:52.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为你可以开欧卡
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.84,0:01:52.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,because within Europe you can drive.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.14,0:01:57.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,卡车运输的费用比空运低多了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.14,0:01:57.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,The cost of shipping by truck is so comparatively low to shipping by plane
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.16,0:02:00.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,车队们可以带着一整个"房子"满欧洲跑
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.16,0:02:00.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,that teams bring whole buildings with them to the European races.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.58,0:02:03.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些房子类似人们常说的"房车"
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.58,0:02:03.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,These buildings are what are modestly referred to as "motorhomes"
Dialogue: 1,0:02:03.66,0:02:06.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,但也能像红牛车队的三层结构那么大
Dialogue: 2,0:02:03.66,0:02:06.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,but can be as large as Red Bull's three story structure
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.36,0:02:10.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,里面包括办公室 休息室 配有完整厨房的餐厅
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.36,0:02:10.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,that includes offices, bars, and a restaurant with a complete kitchen.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.30,0:02:15.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些房子可以打包进几辆卡车中 并可以在两天内组装完成
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.30,0:02:15.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,All of that packs into a number of trucks and can be assembled in less than two days.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:15.24,0:02:19.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些房子会和其他赛车 备件 电子设备等一同
Dialogue: 2,0:02:15.24,0:02:19.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,Along with all the other equipment including cars, spare parts, and electronics,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.42,0:02:24.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,由每个车队的数十辆卡车在欧洲大陆之间穿梭
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.42,0:02:24.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,convoys of dozens of trucks per team criss cross the continent before each European race.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.69,0:02:27.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,正常来讲 比赛的正赛会在每两周的周日进行
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.69,0:02:27.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,Typically races are held every two weekends on Sunday
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.28,0:02:32.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,可以给车队们在大奖赛开始的周四之前足够的准备时间
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.28,0:02:32.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,which gives teams plenty of time to relocate before activity begins on the Thursday before the Grand Prix
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.16,0:02:36.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,但偶尔也会有例外 比赛会在连续的两个周末"背靠背"进行
Dialogue: 2,0:02:32.16,0:02:36.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,but from time to time the schedule is crunched and races take place two weekends in a row.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.78,0:02:41.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,这对车队的物流统筹就是很大的挑战 因为车队们只有三天时间收工
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.78,0:02:41.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,This proves a more daunting logistical challenge as teams only have three full days to break down,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:41.98,0:02:45.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,运输 在新地点重新安装设备
Dialogue: 2,0:02:41.98,0:02:45.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,transport, and reassemble their equipment at the new race site.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.62,0:02:51.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,更要命的是 在2018年首次出现连续三个周末"背靠背靠背"的比赛日
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.62,0:02:51.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even worse, for the first time ever the 2018 season saw three weekends with three races in a row.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:52.00,0:02:55.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,在6月24日法国大奖赛在法国的勒卡斯特雷进行
Dialogue: 2,0:02:52.00,0:02:55.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,On June 24 the French Grand Prix took place in Le Castellet
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.38,0:02:58.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,随后下周来到了奥地利的史匹尔堡
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.38,0:02:58.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,then the next weekend the Austrian one was held in Spielberg
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.06,0:03:01.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,再下周来到了英国银石赛道
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.06,0:03:01.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,finishing off the following weekend with the British Grand Prix in Silverstone.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.50,0:03:07.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,奥地利到英国的运输是最困难的 卡车要开近1000英里
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.50,0:03:07.08,辉 下注,,1050,0,0,,1600公里
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.50,0:03:07.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Austria-UK transfer was the most difficult one as it involved driving nearly 1,000 miles
Dialogue: 1,0:03:07.08,0:03:09.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,其中还要穿越英吉利海峡隧道
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.08,0:03:09.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,including through the choke-point of the channel tunnel.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.92,0:03:12.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,在这趟运输中 每辆卡车由三名司机驾驶
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.92,0:03:12.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,For this trek, each truck was manned by three drivers
Dialogue: 1,0:03:12.58,0:03:16.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,一人开 另外两人在后面的房车中睡觉
Dialogue: 2,0:03:12.58,0:03:16.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that while one drove the others could sleep in an RV that accompanied the convoy.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:16.61,0:03:20.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样卡车除了半路加油外可以不间断行驶
Dialogue: 2,0:03:16.61,0:03:20.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,That way, the trucks could drive continuously only stopping to refuel.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.92,0:03:25.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,但别忘了 这些物流统筹都是相比于海外赛事来说更容易的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.92,0:03:25.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,But again, these races are easy logistically compared to the ones outside of Europe
Dialogue: 1,0:03:25.90,0:03:28.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,海外赛事更难
Dialogue: 2,0:03:25.90,0:03:28.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,—the ones known as flyaway races.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.52,0:03:33.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,就像很多欧洲赛事一样 多数海外赛事也是两周一次
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.52,0:03:33.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just like with the European races the majority of flyaway races occur with two weeks between them
Dialogue: 1,0:03:33.08,0:03:38.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,但偶尔也会有连续两个周末在相隔上千英里的两地"背靠背"办赛的情况
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.08,0:03:38.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,but from time to time races are scheduled on back to back weekends thousands of miles apart.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.34,0:03:44.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些"背靠背"的海外赛事是F1赛季中物流统筹难度最大的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:38.34,0:03:44.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,These back to back flyaway races are the most logistically difficult weeks of the Formula 1 season.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.22,0:03:48.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,在2018年4月8日周日 巴林大奖赛在巴林萨基尔进行
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.22,0:03:48.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,On Sunday April 8th, 2018 the Bahrain Grand Prix was held in Sakhir, Bahrain
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.72,0:03:53.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,七天后的下一个周末 中国大奖赛在中国上海进行
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.72,0:03:53.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,then seven days later, the following weekend, the Chinese Grand Prix was held in Shanghai, China.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.62,0:03:56.61,辉 下注,,0,50,0,,6400公里
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.62,0:03:56.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,两个赛道相距超过4000英里
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.62,0:03:56.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,Over 4,000 miles separated those two racetracks and yet,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:56.61,0:04:01.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,而且和之前一样 一切都要在巴林周日晚上收工
Dialogue: 2,0:03:56.61,0:04:01.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,just like with every race, everything came down on Sunday night in Bahrain
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.19,0:04:04.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,并在中国周四早上重新搭建完成
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.19,0:04:04.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,and had to be operational by Thursday morning in China.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.32,0:04:10.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,更惨的是 上海与巴林有五小时时差 相当于干活时间少了5小时
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.32,0:04:10.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even worse, Shanghai is five hours ahead of Bahrain which is effectively five hours fewer to do the work
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.40,0:04:14.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,但实际上 这场运输的计划早在数月前就开始了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.40,0:04:14.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,but in reality, the planning for this transfer began months before.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:14.56,0:04:18.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,大约在2018年一月 当年赛季揭幕战开始前三个月
Dialogue: 2,0:04:14.56,0:04:18.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,Around January 2018, three months before the first races of the season,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:18.48,0:04:22.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,10支车队都会打包好5套集装箱
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.48,0:04:22.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,each of the ten teams packed up five sets of shipping containers.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.10,0:04:29.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,每一套都有他们海外装备 比如桌椅 电器 厨具和车辆相关工具
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.10,0:04:26.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,Each of these sets held their sea kits carrying things like chairs, tables, appliances,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:26.82,0:04:29.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,cooking utensils, and some elements of their garages.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.70,0:04:33.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些大型 不那么贵重的货物走的是海运
Dialogue: 2,0:04:29.70,0:04:33.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,They send these bulkier and less expensive pieces of equipment by sea
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.22,0:04:36.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为海运比空运便宜到不知道哪里去了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.22,0:04:36.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,as it's massively less expensive than sending them by plane.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.58,0:04:40.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,每组集装箱的具体数量由车队钱包决定 比如红牛就会多一点
Dialogue: 2,0:04:36.58,0:04:40.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,The number of containers per team varies as the wealthier teams like Red Bull will take more
Dialogue: 1,0:04:40.80,0:04:44.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,但平均下来每个车队会带三个40英尺的集装箱
Dialogue: 2,0:04:40.80,0:04:44.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,but in general each team takes about three 40 foot containers.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.60,0:04:46.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,诚然海运非常慢
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.60,0:04:46.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course ocean shipping is slower,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.36,0:04:50.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,但总共有五套 所以总会有一套在正确时间出现在正确地点
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.36,0:04:50.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,but since there are five sets there is always one at the right place at the right time.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:51.02,0:04:55.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,2018年1月 五套装备各自前往前五个海外赛事地点
Dialogue: 2,0:04:51.02,0:04:55.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,That January shipment sent the first five kits to the first five flyaway races
Dialogue: 1,0:04:55.48,0:05:01.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,——澳大利亚墨尔本 巴林萨基尔 中国上海 阿塞拜疆巴库 加拿大蒙特利尔
Dialogue: 2,0:04:55.48,0:05:01.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,—Melbourne, Australia; Sakhir, Bahrain; Shanghai, China; Baku, Azerbaijan; and Montreal, Canada.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.35,0:05:07.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,在每场比赛结束之后 这些装备会重新打包送到下一个海外赛事地点
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.35,0:05:03.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then, as each race was completed
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.06,0:05:07.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,its kit was packed up and sent to the next flyaway race destination without a kit
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.28,0:05:10.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,——澳大利亚那套去新加坡 巴林那套去俄罗斯
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.28,0:05:10.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,—the Australian one went to Singapore, the Bahraini one to Russia,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:10.74,0:05:15.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,中国那套去日本 阿塞拜疆那套去美国 加拿大那套去墨西哥
Dialogue: 2,0:05:10.74,0:05:15.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,the Chinese one to Japan, the Azerbaijani one to the United States, and the Canadian one to Mexico,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.04,0:05:19.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后到了赛季末 这些装备没有新赛场可去
Dialogue: 2,0:05:16.04,0:05:19.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then towards the end of the season, when there are no more tracks to send kits to,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.46,0:05:22.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,于是就运回各自车队的总部"过冬"
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.46,0:05:22.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,they're sent back to the teams' home bases for the winter.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.16,0:05:27.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,在赛场上 F1车队的物流统筹组主要休息时间就是比赛进行的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:05:22.16,0:05:27.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the racetrack, the Formula 1 logistics team's main downtime is actually during the race itself
Dialogue: 1,0:05:27.34,0:05:31.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,但对于巴林到上海这段 物流统筹工作在巴林的周四之前就已经开始了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:27.34,0:05:31.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,but for the Bahrain to China transfer real work began the Thursday before the race.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:31.96,0:05:35.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,从那时起各个车队的物流统筹主管就开始制定收工方案
Dialogue: 2,0:05:31.96,0:05:35.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's when each team's logistics manager started making their tear-down plan—
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.84,0:05:40.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,决定不同零件和设备以哪种顺序 装进哪个集装箱
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.84,0:05:40.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,deciding in which order and into which containers their different pieces of equipment should go.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:40.22,0:05:44.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,当这些完成后 就可以坐等周末比赛结束了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:40.22,0:05:44.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once that was completed there was really not a lot to do until Sunday.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:44.36,0:05:48.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,在周日早上正赛开始之前 打包工作其实就已经开始了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:44.36,0:05:48.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,On Sunday morning, before the race even started, the pack up began.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.32,0:05:50.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,许多备件在正赛的时候用不上
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.32,0:05:50.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Many of the spare parts can't be used during the race—
Dialogue: 1,0:05:50.70,0:05:53.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,大奖赛中不会去换发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:05:50.70,0:05:53.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,they're not going to replace an engine during the Grand Prix—
Dialogue: 1,0:05:53.18,0:05:56.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以它们是第一个被打包走的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:53.18,0:05:56.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,so they're the first pieces of kit to be packed into their containers.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:56.64,0:06:01.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,比赛进行的时候打包工作可能不多 但结束后15分钟内打包便会开始
Dialogue: 2,0:05:56.64,0:06:01.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,Not much happened during the race itself but within 15 minutes of it ending the main pack up began.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:02.00,0:06:08.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,所有设备中最重要的赛车会进行赛后检查 保证其没有进行非法改装
Dialogue: 2,0:06:02.00,0:06:04.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,The cars, the most important pieces of equipment,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:04.48,0:06:08.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,were subjected to a post-race inspection to be sure no illegal modifications were made
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.77,0:06:11.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,而其他所有东西都会立即打包起来
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.77,0:06:11.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,but everything else was immediately ready for packing.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:11.58,0:06:17.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,所有车队希望最先到达目的地的设备会放入三个优先包裹中
Dialogue: 2,0:06:11.58,0:06:17.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,All the equipment that the teams wanted at the destination first were put in one of three priority pallets.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:17.48,0:06:21.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,所有车队的所有优先包裹会率先登上去上海的第一架飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:06:17.48,0:06:21.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Together each team's priority pallets filled up the first plane to Shanghai.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:21.66,0:06:26.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,比赛结束后几小时 当它们打包完成 就会立即被运往机场
Dialogue: 2,0:06:21.66,0:06:26.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,As soon as these were packed they were driven directly to the airport only a few hours after the race ended
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.58,0:06:29.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,准备搭上明天一早飞往上海的飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.58,0:06:29.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,to be prepared for an early morning flight to Shanghai.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:29.22,0:06:33.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,当那架飞机起飞后 赛场上剩余所有东西也都打包完成
Dialogue: 2,0:06:29.22,0:06:33.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,As that plane took off the final pallets were being packed up back at the racetrack.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:33.42,0:06:36.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,在比赛结束仅仅六到八小时后
Dialogue: 2,0:06:33.42,0:06:36.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Only about six to eight hours after the drop of the checkered flag,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:36.86,0:06:39.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,所有东西都整装待发前往机场了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.86,0:06:39.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,all pallets were packed up and on their way to the airport.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:40.12,0:06:46.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,在周一中午 所有6架运送车队设备的波音747都已起飞前往中国
Dialogue: 2,0:06:40.12,0:06:46.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,By midday Monday, all six of the Boeing 747's used to transport the teams equipment to China were in the air.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:46.66,0:06:50.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些飞机是由F1赛事方订的 但钱还是要由车队付
Dialogue: 2,0:06:46.66,0:06:50.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,These planes were chartered by Formula 1 but the teams still pay for the space.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:50.96,0:06:54.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,同时在周一 所有相关人员也启程前往上海
Dialogue: 2,0:06:50.96,0:06:54.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Also on Monday all the staff started their journey to Shanghai.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:54.64,0:06:58.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,多数普通员工会乘坐一般的商业航班
Dialogue: 2,0:06:54.64,0:06:58.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,Many of the lower level staff just flew on normal commercial flights
Dialogue: 1,0:06:58.28,0:07:02.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,而一些高等级的车手则会坐私人飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:06:58.28,0:07:02.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,while some of the higher profile drivers flew private between the two countries.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:02.54,0:07:07.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,九小时的飞行后 第一架飞机在当地傍晚时分落地上海
Dialogue: 2,0:07:02.54,0:07:07.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,After nine hours in the air the first plane touched down in Shanghai around early evening local time.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:07.98,0:07:10.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后卸货交付
Dialogue: 2,0:07:07.98,0:07:10.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,The freight was unloaded and brought to customs.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:10.42,0:07:14.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,午夜时分 所有优先包裹都启程前往赛场
Dialogue: 2,0:07:10.42,0:07:14.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,By midnight, all the priority freight was on its way to the racetrack.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:14.14,0:07:18.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,当晚 负责统筹的工人会把不同车队的优先包裹安置在各自的位置
Dialogue: 2,0:07:14.14,0:07:18.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,Overnight, logistics workers arranged the different teams' freight into their respective paddocks.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:18.90,0:07:22.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,在所有车队的货物都抵达之前 任何车队都不许先碰自己的货物
Dialogue: 2,0:07:18.90,0:07:22.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,No team is allowed to touch their freight until all the other teams' freight has arrived
Dialogue: 1,0:07:22.88,0:07:29.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,一方面是为了公平 一方面是为了安全 让卸货时周围没有闲杂人员
Dialogue: 2,0:07:22.88,0:07:26.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,both for fairness purposes and safety to assure that there aren't many people around
Dialogue: 2,0:07:26.96,0:07:29.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,as pallets are being unloaded and moved.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:29.22,0:07:32.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,在周二早上 组装组的人开始干活
Dialogue: 2,0:07:29.22,0:07:32.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,By Tuesday morning, it's game on for the assembly crews.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:32.36,0:07:36.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,此时每个车队手里有三个优先包裹和之前提到的海外装备
Dialogue: 2,0:07:32.36,0:07:36.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this point each team had their three priority pallets and their sea kit.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:36.32,0:07:40.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,在优先包裹中车队不会放最高价值或者最重要的货物
Dialogue: 2,0:07:36.32,0:07:40.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,In their priority pallets teams didn't put the highest value or most important cargo,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:40.42,0:07:44.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,而是放最先需要组装的设备——P房的框架
Dialogue: 2,0:07:40.42,0:07:44.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,they put the things they needed to assemble first—the bare bones of their garage.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:44.84,0:07:50.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,包括墙面面板 电子系统的核心部分 以及IT 通信的大部分设备
Dialogue: 2,0:07:44.84,0:07:48.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,That includes the wall paneling, the core of their electrical system,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:48.06,0:07:50.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the majority of the IT and communications equipment.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:50.90,0:07:55.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,在周二晚上搭建完成后 赛道再次进行清场 不允许车队接近
Dialogue: 2,0:07:50.90,0:07:55.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,By Tuesday evening that build was done and the track was once again made inaccessible to the teams
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.44,0:07:58.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为次优先包裹会在当天夜里抵达
Dialogue: 2,0:07:55.44,0:07:58.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,as the non-priority pallets were delivered overnight.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:58.32,0:08:01.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,周三早上大约六点 车队抵达赛场
Dialogue: 2,0:07:58.32,0:08:01.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,Early Wednesday morning around 6am the teams arrived back at the track
Dialogue: 1,0:08:01.84,0:08:04.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,开始P房的最后组装工作
Dialogue: 2,0:08:01.84,0:08:04.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,and began work on the final assembly of the garage.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:04.78,0:08:09.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,仅仅四小时后 当天上午晚些时候 所有车队的P房全部进入工作状态
Dialogue: 2,0:08:04.78,0:08:09.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Only after about four hours, by late morning, all the different teams garages were operational.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:09.68,0:08:12.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,十支F1车队只用58小时就成功打包所有设备
Dialogue: 2,0:08:09.68,0:08:12.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,All in all, ten Formula 1 teams successfully packed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.80,0:08:19.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,运输到4000英里外的赛场并重新组装搭建完成
Dialogue: 2,0:08:12.80,0:08:19.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,shipped all their equipment 4,000 miles, and reassembled their paddocks in 58 hours.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:19.08,0:08:21.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,也多亏了精心的统筹工作与工人们的熟练技艺
Dialogue: 2,0:08:19.08,0:08:21.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Thanks to careful planning and practiced workers,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:21.78,0:08:26.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,F1能在每年完美地完成如此壮举
Dialogue: 2,0:08:21.78,0:08:26.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,Formula 1 pulls off this impressive feat every year without a hitch.
